\subsection{Electronic Properties}
In this section, we study the electronic properties of $\mathrm{SrRhO}_{3}$ and $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$ via calculating the energy band structure and density of states. The calculated band structures along the high symmetry lines in Brillion-zone of $\mathrm{SrRhO}_{3}$ and $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$ at zero pressure using PBE-GGA approximation [20] are depicted in Figure 3, where the Fermi level is set at zero eV. In $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$, the valence band maximum (VBM) occurs along the M-point symmetry line, while the conduction band minimum occurs along the $\Gamma$-point symmetry line with energy band gap $3.69 \mathrm{eV}$, resulting in an indirect energy band gap (M-Г) semiconductor.

