The calculated energy band gap is tabulated in Table 2 along with the available previous theoretical value [26]. The calculated energy gap is larger than the theoretical value by $0.32 \mathrm{eV}$ [26]. To the best of our knowledge, there is no experimental value available to compare with. The usual trend of the modified Becke-Johnson potential (mBJ-GGA) method is enlarging the energy band gap values $\left(E_{\mathrm{g}}\right)$ of the semiconductor and insulator materials which makes $E_{\mathrm{g}}$ comparable to the experimental results [21]. The band structures of $\mathrm{SrRhO}_{3}$ and $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$ compounds using mBJ-GGA are displayed in Figure 4. For the $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$ compound, the minimum energy gap within mBJ-GGA is still indirect with the same direction as the PBE-GGA approach, but its value increases by about $0.85 \mathrm{eV}$ to become $4.54 \mathrm{eV}$. $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$ is classified as an insulator within the mBJ-GGA method. $\mathrm{SrRhO}_{3}$ has a metallic nature with no energy gap within the two approaches PBE-GGA and mBJ-GGA.

