\section{Conclusions}
In summary, we have studied the structural, electronic, elastic and optical properties of $\mathrm{SrTMO}_{3}$ $(\mathrm{TM}=\mathrm{Rh}, \mathrm{Zr})$ using the FP-LAPW method within the PBE-GGA and mBJ-GGA approaches in the framework of density functional theory. The lattice parameter is found to be in good agreement with experimental and theoretical results. From the band structure, we found that the $\mathrm{SrRhO}_{3}$ compound has a metallic nature within both BPE-GGA and mBJ-GGA approaches, while $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$ is found to be an insulator within mBJ-GGA, while it is a wide energy band gap semiconductor within PBE-GGA. The elastic constants $\left(C_{11}, C_{12}, C_{44}\right)$, bulk modulus, shear modulus and Young's modulus are also calculated and discussed. By analyzing the $B / S$ ratio and Poisson's ratio, we found that $\mathrm{SrRhO}_{3}$ has a ductile nature, while $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$ has brittle nature. $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$ has a more ionic trend compared to the $\mathrm{SrRhO}_{3}$. The optical properties such as dielectric constant, absorption coefficient, reflectivity coefficient, refractive index, optical conductivity and energy loss function were investigated in the energy range (0-14) $\mathrm{eV}$. According to the dielectric constant, $\mathrm{SrZrO}_{3}$ has a large static dielectric constant which may make it promising as a good dielectric material; while $\mathrm{SrRhO}_{3}$ has a negative real dielectric constant which indicates a metallic behavior. It would be interesting to make detailed measurements of the transport and thermodynamic properties of $\mathrm{SrRhO}_{3}$ under applied fields looking for metamagnetic behavior and non-Fermi-liquid scalings. In conclusion, our theoretical calculations on $\mathrm{SrTMO}_{3}(\mathrm{TM}=\mathrm{Rh}, \mathrm{Zr})$ will help to use these materials for practical applications.

